race.comment: SHADOWFAX (7) went agonisingly close to making it two straight here last start, only denied in the final stride. Draws to advantage again and should roll forward to give another bold sight. BEEN OUR ANGEL (1) has sharp early speed and drops in grade. Gets the 3kg claim to offset the big weight and will be right there applying pressure from the outset. TERRITORIAN (4) resumes off two sharp trials and was well supported throughout his last prep, though only landed the one win. Maps well from the draw and should give a strong account. DE LUCA (8) doesn't win often but is consistently around the mark and finds a suitable race. With the claim helping her in nicely at the weights, she's capable of making her presence felt.
